Sushila’s story is so inspiring! She has not just fulfilled her dream but is helping hundreds of children fulfil their dreams. It’s also inspiring to see the work P&G Shiksha is doing to support education of children. Over its 17 years, P&G Shiksha has supported 2500+ schools which will help 23 lakh+ children. 
I am supporting P&G Shiksha to support education, #YouChooseShiksha too!

#ShikshaForAll #EducationForAll @pgshiksha

It was a memorable experience to join the panel on ‘Shaping Today’s Generation For An Equal Tomorrow’ at @proctergambleindia ‘s #WeSeeEqual summit. We discussed about the role of equal parenting and setting the right examples for the children, and it’s role in creating a future generation of equals. @sakpataudi & I have never defined roles and responsibilities for each other, it has always been about what we enjoyed doing, even in parenting duties. So when it comes to gender biases, the space is already evolving and conversations like these help accelerate the pace of change.

#UnlearnBiases #UnleashEquality

#WeSeeEqual #PGIndia #EqualityAndInclusion

#collaboration @proctergambleindia

Throwback video: Brain freeze is a real thing.. if you don’t trust me then see for yourself 🙈
The slight chill in the mumbai air took me back to this not so memorable moment a few years back 😂

Not my best work, just my first work😬
My first appearance ever, and one that not many know about. Also that is not my voice it was dubbed by someone else.. 
This was the first time I faced the camera in 1989 for a show on Doordarshan called Gul Gulshan Gulfam. My parents were both an integral part of this show playing pivotal roles and I remember going to set with them  in Srinagar and one day asking the director Mr Ved Rahi that i also wanted to be a part of the show and he graciously wrote this cameo for me.

I debuted as a child actor with hum Hain rahi pyar ke which released in 1993 
And today also happens to be 16 years of kalyug the film I debuted with as an adult in 2005 

My mother shared this clip with me sometime ago and it seemed like a day that I wanted to share it with all of you

latestPosts.caption:
Aaila, Iifa!!
Mae abhi bhi debut kar raha hoon😉
Thank you so much @iifa for this honour (best  directorial debut) for Madgaon Express. 
This one is for every single person who believed in me and cheered for me. Thank you for all the love for the film.
Thank you @excelmovies @ritesh_sid @faroutakhtar @roo_cha  @vishalrr  @kassimjagmagia for believing in my script and me as a director and for backing my vision 
Thank you @divyenndu @pratikgandhiofficial @avinashtiwary15 @norafatehi @upendralimaye @chhaya.kadam.75 @remodsouza  and every single actor in the film for having faith in me and surrendering yourself as an actor to my vision. You guys are incredible and made all my characters come to life in the best way possible 
@adilafsarz @thesubaya @hardik.sadhwani @sarveshshingre @prachi.deshpande @sabinahalder @sohelsanwari @zookthespook  and all my technicians for trusting me and helping me bring my vision alive on screen 
Thank you to my family for always being my forever cheerleaders and support system no matter what 
Thank you to all the creators on social media and YouTube for getting behind the film and spreading the good word 
Thank you to all the press and media for covering the film and giving it all the love and appreciation. I take all your feedback and constructive criticism as well and promise to work harder and try to do better in the future 
And above all the audiences for giving the film the occupied seats in the theatre and the love that makes films and film makers who we are ❤️
